Mexico â€™s mining industry will
attract record investment of $4.73 billion this year, the
Mexican Mining Chamber said, according to the state-run news
agency Notimex.  The industry is forecast to receive investment of $4.48
billion next year, Notimex said, according to the chamber.
Sergio Almazan, executive director of the chamber, said about
half of the investment comes from foreign companies, mostly from
